{
  "page": "Gift of mercy",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Hound_gets_no_Mercy_Mike_S_Miller.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/c4/The_Hound_gets_no_Mercy_Mike_S_Miller.jpg/350px-The_Hound_gets_no_Mercy_Mike_S_Miller.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"533\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/c4/The_Hound_gets_no_Mercy_Mike_S_Miller.jpg/525px-The_Hound_gets_no_Mercy_Mike_S_Miller.jpg 1.5x, /images/c/c4/The_Hound_gets_no_Mercy_Mike_S_Miller.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Hound_gets_no_Mercy_Mike_S_Miller.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> refused to give <a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">the Hound</a> the gift of mercy.<br /> Art © Mike S. Miller</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>gift of mercy</b> is the term used for the granting of a quick, humane death to a person who is ailing or mortally wounded and destined to die a painful, lingering death otherwise.  \n</p><p>People may request the gift of mercy.  For example, <a href=\"/index.php/Osha\" title=\"Osha\">Osha</a> grants the dying <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">Maester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Luwin\" title=\"Luwin\">Luwin</a> the gift of mercy at his request.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">Sandor Clegane</a> does the same for a survivor of the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Wedding\" title=\"Red Wedding\">Red Wedding</a>, a bowman in service to Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Marq_Piper\" title=\"Marq Piper\">Marq Piper</a> who escaped but was severely injured.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> gives the gift of mercy to a <a href=\"/index.php/Sarsfield_squire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sarsfield squire\">squire</a> after a brawl at the <a href=\"/index.php/Inn_at_the_Crossroads\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Inn at the Crossroads\">Inn at the Crossroads</a>, but denies mercy to the critically wounded Sandor after stating that he does not deserve it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos74.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos74.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">Beyond the Wall</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_folk\" title=\"Free folk\">free folk</a> will give children the gift of mercy if they have been afflicted by certain diseases, such as <a href=\"/index.php/Greyscale\" title=\"Greyscale\">greyscale</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gift_of_mercy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>If I had given birth to <a href=\"/index.php/Shireen_Baratheon\" title=\"Shireen Baratheon\">that poor child</a>, I would have given her the gift of mercy long ago.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Val\" title=\"Val\">Val</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote> \n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gift_of_mercy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_69\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 69\">Chapter 69</a>, Bran VII.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_65\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 65\">Chapter 65</a>, Arya XII.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos74.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos74.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_74\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 74\">Chapter 74</a>, Arya XIII.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\">4.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_53\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 53\">Chapter 53</a>, Jon XI.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403110135\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.033 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.035 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 435/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8768/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 2069/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 302/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 9/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 2175/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   19.195      1 -total\n 65.14%   12.503      5 Template:Ref\n 40.47%    7.769      5 Template:Ref/core\n 26.55%    5.096      1 Template:References\n 22.45%    4.309      1 Template:Quote\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:13730-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403110135 and revision id 211437\n -->\n",
